.TH VIRTUAL-FLEX 1 "July 2026" "virtual-flex" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
virtual\-flex \- virtual FlexRadio bridge: an Elecraft K4/K4D drives the 4O3A Genius stack over the LAN
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B virtual\-flex
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B sudo virtual\-flex setup
.br
.B sudo virtual\-flex update
.RB [ \-\-check ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B virtual\-flex
impersonates a FLEX\-8600 on the local network so the 4O3A Signature stack
(Power Genius XL, Tuner Genius XL, Antenna Genius XL) discovers and follows an
Elecraft K4/K4D as if it were a FlexRadio: band\-follow, split tracking, and
LAN keying, with no station wiring and no hamlib.
.PP
Frequency, mode, split, and PTT are read natively from the K4's network CAT
port over a single TCP socket, using the K4's auto\-info push mode plus a fast
PTT poll. Runtime updates stream to the stack as terse deltas through a pacing
buffer, matching a real Flex's cadence.
.PP
A presence supervisor mirrors a real radio's lifecycle: when the K4 becomes
unreachable, discovery stops and every stack connection is dropped, so each
Genius box reverts to its configured no\-transceiver antenna (point the
Antenna Genius at a dummy load for lightning safety). When the K4 returns,
service resumes within seconds.
.PP
Run without a command, it starts the bridge daemon (normally done by the
systemd service, not by hand).
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B setup
Interactive configuration wizard. Scans the /24 for the K4 (reading its serial
over CAT) and for the Genius boxes' management ports, offers the findings as
defaults, pins the advertised Flex serial, writes
.IR /etc/virtual\-flex/config.toml ,
and offers to enable and start the service. Re\-running pre\-fills every prompt
from the existing config. Requires root.
.TP
.B update \fR[\fB\-\-check\fR]
Self\-update from the project's GitHub releases: downloads the newest .deb and
installs it via apt, restarting the service only if it was running. With
.B \-\-check
it only reports whether an update exists (no root needed).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-config " " \fIPATH\fR
Path to config.toml (the service uses /etc/virtual\-flex/config.toml).
.TP
.B \-\-host \fIADDR\fR
Bind address for the TCP command server (default 0.0.0.0).
.TP
.B \-\-log\-level \fILEVEL\fR
DEBUG, INFO (default), WARNING, or ERROR. DEBUG traces every status line sent
to each Genius box.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print the version and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/virtual\-flex/config.toml
Generated by the setup wizard; omitted keys inherit built\-in defaults.
Preserved across package upgrades; removed by \fBapt purge\fR.
.TP
.I /usr/lib/systemd/system/virtual\-flex.service
The systemd unit (enable with \fBsystemctl enable \-\-now virtual\-flex\fR).
.SH EXAMPLES
Watch the bridge follow the radio:
.PP
.nf
    journalctl \-u virtual\-flex \-f
.fi
.PP
Check for updates without installing:
.PP
.nf
    virtual\-flex update \-\-check
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR journalctl (1),
.BR systemctl (1)
.PP
Project page and releases: https://github.com/gsa700/virtual\-flex
.SH AUTHOR
AB0R, with Claude (Anthropic).
